- setup curry/web/settings.ini.php
- setup curry/web/settings.local.ini.php from a copy of settings.local.ini.php.sample
- create roles for cenozo db using roles.sql
- use sed to change the default name of curry and cenozo db's as required:
sed -e "s/\(curry\|cenozo\)/dean_\1/g" roles.sql | mysql dean_curry
- log into mastodon, add a service with name="curry", title="Curry"
Version="0,1,0" or whatever version is in curry/web/settings.ini.php
- view details about service "curry" , add Cohort list (tracking, comprehensive)
and Role List entries (administrator, typist)
- create a site in Mastodon: eg., McMaster (curry)
- add user to User List in Mastodon
